# Line ending policy:
# - Keep most text files as LF across platforms (works well with WSL/Linux/macOS).
# - Keep Windows batch scripts as CRLF for cmd.exe compatibility.

# Default for all text: LF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts (explicit).
*.sh text eol=lf
*.command text eol=lf

# Windows batch scripts: CRLF.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf

# Treat binary artifacts as binary (no CRLF conversion).
*.bin -text
